red by the socialist state. Others recall chilling encounters with the police, the law courts, labor camps, and the army. Providing unique insight into the minds and hearts of people who have firsthand experience of China's tumultuous history, this book adds invaluable depth and dimension to our understanding of this rapidly changing country.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aPersonal narratives. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  aalternative history.  aanthropology.  aasia scholars.  aasian studies.  achina.  achinese citizens.  achinese culture.  achinese history.  achinese society.  acommunist party.  acontemporary china.  acultural anthropologists.  acultural perspective.  aeconomic reform.  aethnographers.  ahistorians.  ahistorical.  ahistoriography.  ainterviews.  ajournalism.  anonfiction.  apeoples republic.  apersonal interviews.  apolitical history.  apolitics.  asocial conditions.  asocialism.  asociology.1 aBarmé, Geremie R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarmé, Geremie Randall, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aYe, Sang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093886140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938861423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938861/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles